 * ===============================================================
 *  QUICK SETUP GUIDE  v1.0
 * ===============================================================
 *
 *  1. LIBRARIES  (Sketch > Include Library > Manage Libraries)
 *       "Universal Arduino Telegram Bot"  by Brian Lough
 *       "ArduinoJson"  v6.x  by Benoit Blanchon
 *
 *  2. BOARD MANAGER URL:
 *       https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/
 *       gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
 *       Board            : AI Thinker ESP32-CAM (HW-381 + OV2640)
 *       Partition Scheme : Huge APP (3MB No OTA / 1MB SPIFFS)
 *       CPU Frequency    : 240 MHz
 *
 *  3. FILL IN at top of file:
 *       WIFI_SSID / WIFI_PASS
 *       BOT_TOKEN  (@BotFather on Telegram ? /newbot)
 *       CHAT_ID    (@userinfobot on Telegram)
 *
 *  4. KEY ARCHITECTURE NOTES (v1.0):
 *       + WebServer retained - no library compatibility issues.
 *       + Telegram FreeRTOS task pinned Core 0. tgSend() non-blocking.
 *       + sdMutex guards all SD_MMC calls across both cores.
 *       + Pending-job state machine: apiPhoto/apiRecord return
 *         instantly; executePendingJob() runs the work in loop().
 *         webServer.handleClient() is called during recording so
 *         the dashboard stays responsive even during a 30s video.
 *       + Dashboard gzip: 31 KB -> 8.5 KB PROGMEM (73% smaller).
 *       + Resolution changes always use full camera deinit+reinit.
 *       + CAMERA_GRAB_LATEST with 2 PSRAM buffers prevents overflow.
 *       + AVI dimensions auto-detected from first-frame JPEG SOF.
 *
 *  5. TUNING MOTION SENSITIVITY:
 *       Open Serial Monitor (115200 baud) and watch "[MD] MAD=x.xx"
 *       Idle scene: MAD should be 0.5-3.0
 *       Motion in frame: MAD spikes to 10+
 *       Set MD_THRESHOLD_DEFAULT just above your idle noise value
 *
 *  6. MOTION IS OFF BY DEFAULT
 *       Enable via dashboard "Enable Motion" or /arm in Telegram
 *
 *  7. FILENAMES  (on SD card):
 *       Photos : /photos/YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS.jpg
 *       Videos : /videos/YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS_<RES>_<DUR>s.avi
 *       If NTP not synced: notime_<millis>.jpg / .avi
 * ===============================================================
 */
